               <msContents>
                 <summary>Petition or letter, perhaps official since it mentions petitioning, summons, travel, and the antigrapheus. An Antiochus, Nikanor, and Pythion are mentioned. Possibly part of the Zenon archive.</summary>
                 <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; traces on verso, but practically obliterated.</note>
                     <note type="general">19 lines; broken except at right.</note>
                     <note type="general">See ed. pr. for paleographic notes.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                 </msItemStruct>
